Quote: SNODGALL: <i>see Silverside </i> ... SILVERSIDE A rare inhabitant of our southern waters of yesteryear. ...[244] Completely toothless it was also known as the Snodgall, not to be confused however with Snodgall's Trevalla of which it is no relation. Appears to have largely vanished.
